# EAS Build ignore file — belt-and-suspenders for patterns that
# must never end up in the tar shipped to Expo's build workers,
# even if `.gitignore` or the monorepo-root `.easignore` somehow
# doesn't catch them.
#
# EAS Build uploads the entire monorepo (needed for pnpm
# workspace resolution) and respects both `.gitignore` and
# `.easignore`. When both exist, `.easignore` takes precedence.
#
# Root cause for this file existing: a previous Android build
# (2d6af698-bf27-4bd9-9a7c-34f630ed9bc3) errored in the
# PREPARE_PROJECT phase because tar tried to archive
# `.claude/worktrees/` — the parent of sibling git worktrees
# managed by Claude Code sessions — and those worktrees
# reference files that don't exist in the current checkout's
# index, producing thousands of "Cannot open: No such file or
# directory" errors. `.claude/` has no business in a production
# bundle regardless.

# Claude Code local working directory (worktrees, sessions, logs).
# The leading `..` variant is belt-and-suspenders in case EAS
# ever treats this file's root as `apps/leadsmart-mobile/`
# rather than the monorepo root.
.claude/
../../.claude/

# Local scratch / caches
.turbo/
**/.turbo/
.next/
**/.next/
apps/propertytoolsai/tmp/
apps/propertytoolsai/ml/valuation/artifacts/

# Local env + secrets (already gitignored, but re-assert)
.env
.env.*.local
**/.env
**/.env.*.local
